<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-02-02T10:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-02-02T10:30:00-05:00" n="652" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d652">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">820.7961 Dept. of Commerce Flight/16:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-02-02T12:00:00-03:30"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            2, 1928—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received February 2—11:10
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>7. Your telegram No. 1 of January 7, 8 p.m.<note n="91" xml:id="d652fn91">See footnote 86, <ref target="#pg_811">p.
                                        811</ref>.</note> The Uruguayan Government has granted
                                permission flight to visit Uruguay and to pass over its
                                territories.</p>
                            <p>It is suggested that the use of the word “pathfinding” might give
                                rise to misunderstanding.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>